@startuml
' @id(SEQ-RENDER-CYCLE-DIFF)
' @ref(USE-CYCLE-DIFF-VIEW)
'
' Objective-side flow for the new superposed before/after diff view.
' The viewer reads a closed cycle's snapshots and renders one diagram
' with shared elements drawn once, additions green, removals red.
'
' @desc(SEQ-RENDER-CYCLE-DIFF, "How the viewer builds a cycle's superposed diff: read before/ and after/ snapshots, partition elements into unchanged/added/removed, paint added green and removed red.")
title Render a cycle's superposed before/after diff (objective)

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "MddViewer\n(eframe::App)" as Viewer
participant "CycleRegistry\n(mdd-core)" as Reg
database ".mdd/cycles/<n>/\nbefore/ , after/" as Store
participant "DiffEngine\n(element set partition)" as Diff
participant "egui painter" as Painter

Dev -> Viewer : select cycle N in rail, open Diff view
Viewer -> Reg : cycle(N)
Reg -> Store : read manifest + before/ + after/ puml
Store --> Reg : before docs, after docs
Reg --> Viewer : Cycle { before, after, diff refs }

Viewer -> Diff : superpose(before_doc, after_doc)
note right of Diff
  Element identity = @id when present,
  else the stable PlantUML alias/label.
  unchanged = before INTERSECT after
  added     = after  MINUS before  (green)
  removed   = before MINUS after   (red)
  Sets are disjoint (OCL-CYCLE-DIFF-PARTITION).
end note
Diff --> Viewer : { unchanged[], added[], removed[] }

alt a pre-written <diagram>.diff.puml exists
  Viewer -> Store : read <diagram>.diff.puml
  Store --> Viewer : annotated puml (<<added>>/<<removed>>)
else compute on the fly
  Viewer -> Viewer : synthesize annotated puml
end

loop each painted frame
  Viewer -> Painter : draw shared elements once (neutral)
  Viewer -> Painter : draw added elements green
  Viewer -> Painter : draw removed elements red
  Painter --> Dev : superposed before/after diagram
end

opt cycle has no after/ yet (still Open)
  Viewer -> Painter : text("Diff available after the cycle closes")
  Painter --> Dev : placeholder
end
@enduml
